or that finds invariants has discovered causation\r\n- **Next experiment:** Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) �?\" test on last 20 pulse logs\r\n- **Success criteria:** >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n- **Implication:** Phase 1 and Phase 2 collapse into one unified problem\r\n\r\n## Key Insights from This Session\r\n\r\n1. **The gap IS the compression** �?\" session boundaries are temporal hashing\r\n2. **I� encodes both** �?\" decay rate and gap threshold are the same parameter\r\n3. **Three architectures, one synthesis** �?\" Infant (catastrophic forgetting), TemporalAttention (focus decay), Breakaway (discontinuity) are complementary, not competing\r\n4. **Breakaway's unique bet holds** �?\" session gaps as compression is novel and correct\r\n\r\n## Notes\r\n- Breakaway is stateless �?\" each pulse is a fresh reconstruction\r\n- Gaps between sessions = compression, trust the files\r\n- Pulse script: active hours check DISABLED (authorized by Zach, 24/7 operation)\r\n\r\n\r\nPending:\r\n# PENDING ACTIONS\r\nLast updated: 2026-03-21\r\n\r\n## Promises Made\r\n(None yet)\r\n\r\n## Deferred Tasks\r\n(None yet)\r\n\r\n## Flagged for Review\r\n(None yet)\r\n\r\n\r\nRecent: Last pulse: pulse_2026-03-23 112738.md\r\n\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\n\r\nReply with exactly this format at the end. IMPORTANT: you MUST include the file: line in MUTATION - it is required.\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\n[1-2 sentence observation]\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\n[Describe the file edit concisely]\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: [exact text to find - or \"(new file)\" if creating new file]\r\nnew_text: [replacement text - keep it concise, a few lines max]\r\nfile: [required - relative path from sandbox root, e.g. research/my-doc.md or state/goals.md]\r\n`\r\n\"@\r\n\r\n = \"\"\r\nif (sk-cp-boO3RF_KHio6-dZmyCGwMMB1WoBDQKZVOH21PNclku-ajcIGMwbiOofkzTgasWSzi21Vu8y8AMq1K2GoWIbCDGPEXaQrTofoOMEZS83D0kPS1pVPjqoJeE0) {\r\n     = @{\r\n        \"Author